

Array ADT (Abstract Data type)


Data and Operations:

Representation of Data: (We use struct for this)
	1.Array space
	2.Size
	3.Length (no. of elements)
	
Operations:
	1. Display()- traversing through an array 1:1
	
	2. Add(x) / Append(x)- Adding/ appending an element at the end of the array.
	
	3. Insert( index, x)- For the given index, shift all the elements right, and place x at index.	
	 psuedo code: 								
		for(i=length; i>index; i--)					
		{											Time Complexity:
			A[i] = A[i-1];							min: O(1)
		}											max: O(n)
		
		A[index] = x;
		length ++;
	
	
	4. Delete(index)- Deleting an element at a given index.
	
	5. Search(x)
	6. Get(index)
	7. Set(index, x)
	8. Max()/ Min()
	9. Reverse()
	10.Shif()/ Rotate()
	
	